quran[36]{c,v,t}:
  56,39,A multitude from the ancients
  56,40,And a multitude from the later generations
  56,41,And the fellows on the left hand; how miserable Shall the fellows on the left hand be
  56,42,Amidst scorching wind and scalding water
  56,43,And the shade of black smoke
  56,44,Neither cool nor pleasant
  56,45,Verily they have been heretofore affluent
  56,46,And they have been persisting in the heinous offence
  56,47,"And they were wont to say: when we have died and become dust and bones, shall we, then, verily be raised"
  56,48,We and our fathers of old
  56,49,"Say thou: verily the ancients and those of later generations"
  56,50,Are going to be assembled on the appointed time of a Day Known
  56,51,"Then verily ye, O ye erring, denying people"
  56,52,Shall surely eat of the tree of Az-Zqqum
  56,53,And shall fill therewith your bellies
  56,54,And shall be drinkers thereon of boiling water
  56,55,Drinkers even as the drinking of thirsty camels
  56,56,This shall be their entertainment on the Day of Requital
  56,57,"We! it is We Who created you: wherefore confess ye not"
  56,58,Behold! - that which ye emit
  56,59,"Create him ye, or are We the Creator"
  56,60,We! it is We Who have decreed death Unto you all. And We are not to be outrun
  56,61,That We may substitute others like Unto you and produce you into that which ye know not
  56,62,And assuredly ye have fully known the first Production Wherefore heed ye not
  56,63,Behold! - that which ye sow
  56,64,"Cause it ye to grow, or are We the Grower"
  56,65,"If We willed, surely We would make it chaff, so that ye would be left wondering"
  56,66,Verily we are undone
  56,67,Aye! we are deprived
  56,68,Behold! - the water which ye drink
  56,69,"Send it down ye from the raincloud, or are We the Sender down"
  56,70,"If We willed, surely We would make it brackish. Wherefore give ye not thanks"
  56,71,Behold! - the fire which ye strike out
  56,72,"Produce ye the tree thereof, or are We the Producer"
  56,73,We! it is We Who made it a reminder and a provision Unto the campers
  56,74,"Wherefore hallow thou the name of thy Lord, the Mighty"